Junior Accounts Clerk - Singapore International School (SIS Group of Schools)
Junior Accounts Clerk  -
Junior Accounts Clerk
Responsibilities
Compile and analyze financial information to prepare entries to accounts, such as general ledger accounts, and document business transactionsTo execute monthly accounts closing and preparation of financial statementsContinous improvement in the financial closing process in terms of quality and timeliness.Handling and safeguarding of cash receipt including end of day closing.Assist the preparation of monthly financial reporting package.Monitoring Receivables and Collection function; controlling payables.Reconciliations functions, financial reports and any other related tasks assigned by the Accounting and Finance Manager.Assist in the facilitation in the filling of annual statutory report, and tax filling. Job RequirmentS1 or Diploma degree in Accounting.Minimum 1 years of working experience in Accounting.Fresh graduates are also welcome to apply.Fluent in both oral and written in English is a necessary.Good computer skills.Strong analytical skills, detail oriented, good business exposure, communication skill, decision making, and good leadership skill.This position will be posted in Bonavista, Lebak Bulus, South Jakarta.  We offer a strong commitment to professional development provide a clear career development path in a rapidly expanding organization for the right candidatesIf you feel you can offer the qualities we are looking for please forward your CV (not more than 1 week), supporting documents, two referees, recent photograph, and expected salary along with an introductory letter to: Singapore International School (Indonesia)hrbv@sisschools.org
